msgid "fish 3.6.2 (released December 4, 2023)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:161
msgid ""
"This release of fish contains a security fix for CVE-2023-49284, a minor "
"security problem identified in fish 3.6.1 and previous versions (thought to "
"affect all released versions of fish)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:164
msgid ""
"fish uses certain Unicode non-characters internally for marking wildcards "
"and expansions. It incorrectly allowed these markers to be read on command "
"substitution output, rather than transforming them into a safe internal "
"representation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:168
msgid ""
"For example, ``echo \\UFDD2HOME`` has the same output as ``echo $HOME``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:170
msgid ""
"While this may cause unexpected behavior with direct input, this may become "
"a minor security problem if the output is being fed from an external program "
"into a command substitution where this output may not be expected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:177
msgid "fish 3.6.1 (released March 25, 2023)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:179
msgid ""
"This release of fish contains a number of fixes for problems identified in "
"fish 3.6.1, as well as some enhancements."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:183
msgid ""
"``abbr --erase`` now also erases the universal variables used by the old "
"abbr function. That means::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:184
msgid "abbr --erase (abbr --list)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:186
msgid "can now be used to clean out all old abbreviations (:issue:`9468`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:187
msgid ""
"``abbr --add --universal`` now warns about ``--universal`` being non-"
"functional, to make it easier to detect old-style ``abbr`` calls (:issue:"
"`9475`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:191
msgid ""
"The Web-based configuration for abbreviations has been removed, as it was "
"not functional with the changes abbreviations introduced in 3.6.0 (:issue:"
"`9460`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:195
msgid ""
"``abbr --list`` no longer escapes the abbr name, which is necessary to be "
"able to pass it to ``abbr --erase`` (:issue:`9470`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:196
msgid ""
"``read`` will now print an error if told to set a read-only variable, "
"instead of silently doing nothing (:issue:`9346`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:197
msgid "``set_color -v`` no longer crashes fish (:issue:`9640`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:201
msgid ""
"Using ``fish_vi_key_bindings`` in combination with fish's ``--no-config`` "
"mode works without locking up the shell (:issue:`9443`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:202
msgid ""
"The history pager now uses more screen space, usually half the screen (:"
"issue:`9458`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:203
msgid ""
"Variables that were set while the locale was C (the default ASCII-only "
"locale) will now properly be encoded if the locale is switched (:issue:"
"`2613`, :issue:`9473`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:204
msgid ""
"Escape during history search restores the original command line again "
"(fixing a regression in 3.6.0)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:205
msgid ""
"Using ``--help`` on builtins now respects the ``$MANPAGER`` variable, in "
"preference to ``$PAGER`` (:issue:`9488`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:206
msgid ""
":kbd:`Control-G` closes the history pager, like other shells (:issue:`9484`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:207
msgid ""
"The documentation for the ``:``, ``[`` and ``.`` builtin commands can now be "
"looked up with ``man`` (:issue:`9552`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:208
msgid ""
"fish no longer crashes when searching history for non-ASCII codepoints case-"
"insensitively (:issue:`9628`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:209
msgid ""
"The :kbd:`Alt-S` binding will now also use ``please`` if available (:issue:"
"`9635`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:210
msgid ""
"Themes that don't specify every color option can be installed correctly in "
"the Web-based configuration (:issue:`9590`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:211
msgid ""
"Compatibility with Midnight Commander's prompt integration has been improved "
"(:issue:`9540`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:212
msgid ""
"A spurious error, noted when using fish in Google Drive directories under "
"WSL 2, has been silenced (:issue:`9550`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:213
msgid ""
"Using ``read`` in ``fish_greeting`` or similar functions will not trigger an "
"infinite loop (:issue:`9564`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:214
msgid ""
"Compatibility when upgrading from old versions of fish (before 3.4.0) has "
"been improved (:issue:`9569`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:218
msgid ""
"The git prompt will compute the stash count to be used independently of the "
"informative status (:issue:`9572`)."
msgstr ""

