msgid ""
"Windows' ``color`` (:issue:`8483`), ``attrib``, ``attributes``, ``choice``, "
"``clean``, ``cleanmgr``, ``cmd``, ``cmdkey``, ``comp``, ``forfiles``, "
"``powershell``, ``reg``, ``schtasks``, ``setx`` (:issue:`8486`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:815
msgid "``zef`` (:issue:`8114`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:817
msgid ""
"Improvements to many completions, especially for ``git`` aliases (:issue:"
"`8129`), subcommands (:issue:`8134`) and submodules (:issue:`8716`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:818
msgid ""
"Many adjustments to complete correct options for system utilities on BSD and "
"macOS."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:819
msgid ""
"When evaluating custom completions, the command line state no longer "
"includes variable overrides (``var=val``). This unbreaks completions that "
"read ``commandline -op``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:823
msgid "Dynamic terminal titles are enabled on WezTerm (:issue:`8121`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:824
msgid ""
"Directory history navigation works out of the box with Apple Terminal's "
"default key settings (:issue:`2330`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:825
msgid ""
"fish now assumes Unicode 9+ widths for emoji under iTerm 2 (:issue:`8200`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:826
msgid ""
"Skin-tone emoji modifiers (U+1F3FB through U+1F3FF) are now measured as "
"width 0 (:issue:`8275`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:827
msgid "fish's escape sequence removal now also knows Tmux's wrapped escapes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:828
msgid "Vi mode cursors are enabled in Apple Terminal.app (:issue:`8167`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:829
msgid ""
"Vi cursor shaping and $PWD reporting is now also enabled on foot (:issue:"
"`8422`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:830
msgid ""
"``ls`` will use colors also on newer versions of Apple Terminal.app (:issue:"
"`8309`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:831
msgid ""
"The :kbd:`Delete` and :kbd:`Shift-Tab` keys work more reliably under ``st`` "
"(:issue:`8352`, :issue:`8354`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:835
msgid ""
"Fish's test suite now uses ``ctest``, and has become much faster to run. It "
"is now also possible to run only specific tests with targets named "
"``test_$filename`` - ``make test_set.fish`` only runs the set.fish test. (:"
"issue:`7851`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:836
msgid ""
"The HTML version of the documentation now includes copy buttons for code "
"examples (:issue:`8218`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:837
msgid ""
"The HTML version of the documentation and the web-based configuration tool "
"now pick more modern system fonts instead of falling back to Arial and "
"something like Courier New most of the time (:issue:`8632`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:838
msgid ""
"The Debian & Ubuntu package linked from fishshell.com is now a single "
"package, rather than split into ``fish`` and ``fish-common`` (:issue:`7845`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:839
msgid ""
"The macOS installer does not assert that Rosetta is required to install fish "
"on machines with Apple Silicon (:issue:`8566`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:840
msgid ""
"The macOS installer now cleans up previous .pkg installations when "
"upgrading. (:issue:`2963`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:844
msgid "The minimum version of CMake required to build fish is now 3.5.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:845
msgid ""
"The CMake installation supports absolute paths for ``CMAKE_INSTALL_DATADIR`` "
"(:issue:`8150`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:846
msgid "Building using NetBSD curses works on any platform (:issue:`8087`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:847
msgid ""
"The build system now uses the default linker instead of forcing use of the "
"gold or lld linker (:issue:`8152`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:852
msgid "fish 3.3.1 (released July 6, 2021)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:854
msgid ""
"This release of fish fixes the following problems identified in fish 3.3.0:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:856
msgid ""
"The prompt and command line are redrawn correctly in response to universal "
"variable changes (:issue:`8088`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:857
msgid ""
"A superfluous error that was produced when setting the ``PATH`` or "
"``CDPATH`` environment variables to include colon-delimited components that "
"do not exist was removed (:issue:`8095`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:858
msgid ""
"The Vi mode indicator in the prompt is repainted correctly after :kbd:`Ctrl-"
"C` cancels the current command (:issue:`8103`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:859
msgid ""
"fish builds correctly on platforms that do not have a ``spawn.h`` header, "
"such as old versions of OS X (:issue:`8097`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:861
msgid ""
"A number of improvements to the documentation, and fixes for completions, "
"are included as well."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:863
msgid ""
"If you are upgrading from version 3.2.2 or before, please also review the "
"release notes for 3.3.0 (included below)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:868
msgid "fish 3.3.0 (released June 28, 2021)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:873
msgid ""
"``fish_config`` gained a ``prompt`` subcommand to show and pick from the "
"sample prompts directly in the terminal, instead of having to open a "
"webbrowser. For example ``fish_config prompt choose default`` loads the "
"default prompt in the current session (:issue:`7958`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:874
msgid ""
"The documentation has been reorganized to be easier to understand (:issue:"
"`7773`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:878
msgid ""
"The ``$fish_history`` value \"default\" is no longer special. It used to be "
"treated the same as \"fish\" (:issue:`7650`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:879
msgid ""
"Redirection to standard error with the ``^`` character has been disabled by "
"default. It can be turned back on using the ``stderr-nocaret`` feature flag, "
"but will eventually be disabled completely (:issue:`7105`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:880
msgid ""
"Specifying an initial tab to ``fish_config`` now only works with "
"``fish_config browse`` (eg ``fish_config browse variables``), otherwise it "
"would interfere with the new ``prompt`` subcommand (see below) (:issue:"
"`7958`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:884
msgid ""
"``math`` gained new functions ``log2`` (like the documentation claimed), "
"``max`` and ``min`` (:issue:`7856`). ``math`` functions can be used without "
"the parentheses (eg ``math sin 2 + 6``), and functions have the lowest "
"precedence in the order of operations (:issue:`7877`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:885
msgid ""
"Shebang (``#!``) lines are no longer required within shell scripts, "
"improving support for scripts with concatenated binary contents. If a file "
"fails to execute and passes a (rudimentary) binary safety check, fish will "
"re-invoke it using ``/bin/sh`` (:issue:`7802`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:886
msgid ""
"Exit codes are better aligned with bash. A failed execution now reports "
"``$status`` of 127 if the file is not found, and 126 if it is not executable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:887
msgid ""
"``echo`` no longer writes its output one byte at a time, improving "
"performance and allowing use with Linux's special API files (``/proc``, ``/"
"sys`` and such) (:issue:`7836`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:888
msgid ""
"fish should now better handle ``cd`` on filesystems with broken ``stat(3)`` "
"responses (:issue:`7577`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:889
msgid ""
"Builtins now properly report a ``$status`` of 1 upon unsuccessful writes (:"
"issue:`7857`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:890
msgid ""
"``string match`` with unmatched capture groups and without the ``--all`` "
"flag now sets an empty variable instead of a variable containing the empty "
"string. It also correctly imports the first match if multiple arguments are "
"provided, matching the documentation. (:issue:`7938`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:891
msgid ""
"fish produces more specific errors when a command in a command substitution "
"wasn't found or is not allowed. This now prints something like \"Unknown "
"command\" instead of \"Unknown error while evaluating command substitution\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:892
msgid ""
"``fish_indent`` allows inline variable assignments (``FOO=BAR command``) to "
"use line continuation, instead of joining them into one line (:issue:`7955`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:893
msgid ""
"fish gained a ``--no-config`` option to disable configuration files. This "
"applies to user-specific and the systemwide ``config.fish`` (typically in ``/"
"etc/fish/config.fish``), and configuration snippets (typically in ``conf.d`` "
"directories). It also disables universal variables, history, and loading of "
"functions from system or user configuration directories (:issue:`7921`, :"
"issue:`1256`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:894
msgid ""
"When universal variables are unavailable for some reason, setting a "
"universal variable now sets a global variable instead (:issue:`7921`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:895
msgid ""
"``$last_pid`` now contains the process ID of the last process in the "
"pipeline, allowing it to be used in scripts (:issue:`5036`, :issue:`5832`, :"
"issue:`7721`). Previously, this value contained the process group ID, but in "
"scripts this was the same as the running fish's process ID."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:896
msgid ""
"``process-exit`` event handlers now receive the same value as ``$status`` in "
"all cases, instead of receiving -1 when the exit was due to a signal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:897
msgid ""
"``process-exit`` event handlers for PID 0 also received ``JOB_EXIT`` events; "
"this has been fixed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:898
msgid ""
"``job-exit`` event handlers may now be created with any of the PIDs from the "
"job. The handler is passed the last PID in the job as its second argument, "
"instead of the process group."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:899
msgid ""
"Trying to set an empty variable name with ``set`` no longer works (these "
"variables could not be used in expansions anyway)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:900
msgid ""
"``fish_add_path`` handles an undefined ``PATH`` environment variable "
"correctly (:issue:`8082`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:904
msgid ""
"Commands entered before the previous command finishes will now be properly "
"syntax highlighted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:905
msgid ""
"fish now automatically creates ``config.fish`` and the configuration "
"directories in ``$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/fish`` (by default ``~/.config/fish``) if "
"they do not already exist (:issue:`7402`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:906
msgid ""
"``$SHLVL`` is no longer incremented in non-interactive shells. This means it "
"won't be set to values larger than 1 just because your environment happens "
"to run some scripts in $SHELL in its startup path (:issue:`7864`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:907
msgid ""
"fish no longer rings the bell when flashing the command line. The flashing "
"should already be enough notification and the bell can be annoying (:issue:"
"`7875`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:908
msgid ""
"``fish --help`` is more helpful if the documentation isn't installed (:issue:"
"`7824`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:909
msgid ""
"``funced`` won't include an entry on where a function is defined, thanks to "
"the new ``functions --no-details`` option (:issue:`7879`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:910
msgid ""
"A new variable, ``fish_killring``, containing entries from the killring, is "
"now available (:issue:`7445`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:911
msgid ""
"``fish --private`` prints a note on private mode on startup even if "
"``$fish_greeting`` is an empty list (:issue:`7974`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:912
msgid ""
"fish no longer attempts to lock history or universal variable files on "
"remote filesystems, including NFS and Samba mounts. In rare cases, updates "
"to these files may be dropped if separate fish instances modify them "
"simultaneously. (:issue:`7968`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:913
msgid ""
"``wait`` and ``on-process-exit`` work correctly with jobs that have already "
"exited (:issue:`7210`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:914
msgid ""
"``__fish_print_help`` (used for ``--help`` output for fish's builtins) now "
"respects the ``LESS`` environment variable, and if not set, uses better "
"default pager settings (:issue:`7997`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:915
msgid ""
"Errors from ``alias`` are now printed to standard error, matching other "
"builtins and functions (:issue:`7925`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:916
msgid ""
"``ls`` output is colorized on OpenBSD if colorls utility is installed (:"
"issue:`8035`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:917
msgid ""
"The default pager color looks better in terminals with light backgrounds (:"
"issue:`3412`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:918
msgid ""
"Further robustness improvements to the bash history import (:issue:`7874`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:919
msgid ""
"fish now tries to find a Unicode-aware locale for encoding (``LC_CTYPE``) if "
"started without any locale information, improving the display of emoji and "
"other non-ASCII text on misconfigured systems (:issue:`8031`). To allow a C "
"locale, set the variable ``fish_allow_singlebyte_locale`` to 1."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:920
msgid ""
"The Web-based configuration and documentation now feature a dark mode if the "
"browser requests it (:issue:`8043`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:921
msgid ""
"Color variables can now also be given like ``--background red`` and ``-b "
"red``, not just ``--background=red`` (:issue:`8053`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:922
msgid "``exit`` run within ``fish_prompt`` now exits properly (:issue:`8033`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:923
msgid ""
"When attempting to execute the unsupported POSIX-style brace command group "
"(``{ ... }``) fish will suggest its equivalent ``begin; ...; end`` commands "
"(:issue:`6415`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:927
msgid ""
"Pasting in Vi mode puts text in the right place in normal mode (:issue:"
"`7847`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:928
msgid ""
"Vi mode's :kbd:`u` is bound to ``undo`` instead of ``history-search-"
"backward``, following GNU readline's behavior. Similarly, :kbd:`Control-R` "
"is bound to ``redo`` instead of ``history-search-backward``, following Vim (:"
"issue:`7908`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:929
msgid ""
":kbd:`s` in Vi visual mode now does the same thing as :kbd:`c` (:issue:"
"`8039`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:930
msgid ""
"The binding for :kbd:`\"*y` now uses ``fish_clipboard_copy``, allowing it to "
"support more than just ``xsel``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:931
msgid ""
"The :kbd:`Control-Space` binding can be correctly customised (:issue:`7922`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:932
msgid "``exit`` works correctly in bindings (:issue:`7967`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:933
msgid ""
"The :kbd:`F1` binding, which opens the manual page for the current command, "
"now works around a bug in certain ``less`` versions that fail to clear the "
"screen (:issue:`7863`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:934
msgid ""
"The binding for :kbd:`Alt-S` now toggles whether ``sudo`` is prepended, even "
"when it took the commandline from history instead of only adding it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:935
msgid ""
"The new functions ``fish_commandline_prepend`` and "
"``fish_commandline_append`` allow toggling the presence of a prefix/suffix "
"on the current commandline. (:issue:`7905`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:936
msgid ""
"``backward-kill-path-component`` :kbd:`Control-W`) no longer erases parts of "
"two tokens when the cursor is positioned immediately after ``/``. (:issue:"
"`6258`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:940
msgid ""
"The default Vi mode prompt now uses foreground instead of background colors, "
"making it less obtrusive (:issue:`7880`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:941
msgid ""
"Performance of the \"informative\" git prompt is improved somewhat (:issue:"
"`7871`). This is still slower than the non-informative version by its very "
"nature. In particular it is IO-bound, so it will be very slow on slow disks "
"or network mounts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:942
msgid ""
"The sample prompts were updated. Some duplicated prompts, like the various "
"classic variants, or less useful ones, like the \"justadollar\" prompt were "
"removed, some prompts were cleaned up, and in some cases renamed. A new "
"\"simple\" and \"disco\" prompt were added (:issue:`7884`, :issue:`7897`, :"
"issue:`7930`). The new prompts will only take effect when selected and "
"existing installed prompts will remain unchanged."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:943
msgid ""
"A new ``prompt_login`` helper function to describe the kind of "
"\"login\" (user, host and chroot status) for use in prompts. This replaces "
"the old \"debian chroot\" prompt and has been added to the default and "
"terlar prompts (:issue:`7932`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:944
msgid ""
"The Web-based configuration's prompt picker now shows and installs right "
"prompts (:issue:`7930`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:945
msgid ""
"The git prompt now has the same symbol order in normal and \"informative\" "
"mode, and it's customizable via ``$__fish_git_prompt_status_order`` (:issue:"
"`7926`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:951
msgid "``firewall-cmd`` (:issue:`7900`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:952
msgid "``sv`` (:issue:`8069`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:954
msgid "Improvements to plenty of completions!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:955
msgid ""
"Commands that wrap ``cd`` (using ``complete --wraps cd``) get the same "
"completions as ``cd`` (:issue:`4693`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:956
msgid ""
"The ``--force-files`` option to ``complete`` works for bare arguments, not "
"just options (:issue:`7920`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:957
msgid ""
"Completion descriptions for functions don't include the function definition, "
"making them more concise (:issue:`7911`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:958
msgid "The ``kill`` completions no longer error on MSYS2 (:issue:`8046`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:959
msgid ""
"Completion scripts are now loaded when calling a command via a relative path "
"(like ``./git``) (:issue:`6001`, :issue:`7992`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:960
msgid ""
"When there are multiple completion candidates, fish inserts their shared "
"prefix. This prefix was computed in a case-insensitive way, resulting in "
"wrong case in the completion pager. This was fixed by only inserting "
"prefixes with matching case (:issue:`7744`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:964
msgid ""
"fish no longer tries to detect a missing new line during startup, preventing "
"an erroneous ``⏎`` from appearing if the terminal is resized at the wrong "
"time, which can happen in tiling window managers (:issue:`7893`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:965
msgid ""
"fish behaves better when it disagrees with the terminal on the width of "
"characters. In particular, staircase effects with right prompts should be "
"gone in most cases (:issue:`8011`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:966
msgid ""
"If the prompt takes up the entire line, the last character should no longer "
"be chopped off in certain terminals (:issue:`8002`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:967
msgid ""
"fish's reflow handling has been disabled by default for kitty (:issue:"
"`7961`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:968
msgid ""
"The default prompt no longer produces errors when used with a dumb terminal "
"(:issue:`7904`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:969
msgid ""
"Terminal size variables are updated for window size change signal handlers "
"(``SIGWINCH``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:970
msgid ""
"Pasting within a multi-line command using a terminal that supports bracketed "
"paste works correctly, instead of producing an error (:issue:`7782`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:971
msgid ""
"``set_color`` produces an error when used with invalid arguments, rather "
"than empty output which interacts badly with Cartesian product expansion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:975
msgid ""
"fish runs correctly on platforms without the ``O_CLOEXEC`` flag for "
"``open(2)`` (:issue:`8023`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:980
msgid "fish 3.2.2 (released April 7, 2021)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:982
msgid ""
"This release of fish fixes a number of additional issues identified in the "
"fish 3.2 series:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:984
msgid ""
"The command-not-found handler used suggestions from ``pacman`` on Arch "
"Linux, but this caused major slowdowns on some systems and has been disabled "
"(:issue:`7841`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:985
msgid ""
"fish will no longer hang on exit if another process is in the foreground on "
"macOS (:issue:`7901`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:986
msgid ""
"Certain programs (such as ``lazygit``) could create situations where fish "
"would not receive keystrokes correctly, but it is now more robust in these "
"situations (:issue:`7853`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:987
msgid ""
"Arguments longer than 1024 characters no longer trigger excessive CPU usage "
"on macOS (:issue:`7837`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:988
msgid ""
"fish builds correctly on macOS when using new versions of Xcode (:issue:"
"`7838`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:989
msgid ""
"Completions for ``aura`` (:issue:`7865`) and ``tshark`` (:issue:`7858`) "
"should no longer produce errors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:990
msgid ""
"Background jobs no longer interfere with syntax highlighting (a regression "
"introduced in fish 3.2.1, :issue:`7842`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:992
msgid ""
"If you are upgrading from version 3.1.2 or before, please also review the "
"release notes for 3.2.1 and 3.2.0 (included below)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:997
msgid "fish 3.2.1 (released March 18, 2021)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:999
msgid ""
"This release of fish fixes the following problems identified in fish 3.2.0:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1001
msgid ""
"Commands in key bindings are run with fish's internal terminal modes, "
"instead of the terminal modes typically used for commands. This fixes a bug "
"introduced in 3.2.0, where text would unexpectedly appear on the terminal, "
"especially when pasting (:issue:`7770`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1002
msgid ""
"Prompts which use the internal ``__fish_print_pipestatus`` function will "
"display correctly rather than carrying certain modifiers (such as bold) "
"further than intended (:issue:`7771`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1003
msgid ""
"Redirections to internal file descriptors is allowed again, reversing the "
"changes in 3.2.0. This fixes a problem with Midnight Commander (:issue:"
"`7769`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1004
msgid ""
"Universal variables should be fully reliable regardless of operating system "
"again (:issue:`7774`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1005
msgid ""
"``fish_git_prompt`` no longer causes screen flickering in certain terminals "
"(:issue:`7775`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1006
msgid ""
"``fish_add_path`` manipulates the ``fish_user_paths`` variable correctly "
"when moving multiple paths (:issue:`7776`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1007
msgid ""
"Pasting with a multi-line command no longer causes a "
"``__fish_tokenizer_state`` error (:issue:`7782`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1008
msgid ""
"``psub`` inside event handlers cleans up temporary files properly (:issue:"
"`7792`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1009
msgid ""
"Event handlers declared with ``--on-job-exit $fish_pid`` no longer run "
"constantly (:issue:`7721`), although these functions should use ``--on-event "
"fish_exit`` instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1010
msgid "Changing terminal modes inside ``config.fish`` works (:issue:`7783`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1011
msgid ""
"``set_color --print-colors`` no longer prints all colors in bold (:issue:"
"`7805`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1012
msgid ""
"Completing commands starting with a ``-`` no longer prints an error (:issue:"
"`7809`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1013
msgid ""
"Running ``fish_command_not_found`` directly no longer produces an error on "
"macOS or other OSes which do not have a handler available (:issue:`7777`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1014
msgid ""
"The new ``type`` builtin now has the (deprecated) ``--quiet`` long form of "
"``-q`` (:issue:`7766`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1016
msgid "It also includes some small enhancements:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1018
msgid ""
"``help`` and ``fish_config`` work correctly when fish is running in a Chrome "
"OS Crostini Linux VM (:issue:`7789`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1019
msgid ""
"The history file can be made a symbolic link without it being overwritten (:"
"issue:`7754`), matching a similar improvement for the universal variable "
"file in 3.2.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1020
msgid ""
"An unhelpful error (\"access: No error\"), seen on Cygwin, is no longer "
"produced (:issue:`7785`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1021
msgid ""
"Improvements to the ``rsync`` completions (:issue:`7763`), some completion "
"descriptions (:issue:`7788`), and completions that use IP address (:issue:"
"`7787`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1022
msgid "Improvements to the appearance of ``fish_config`` (:issue:`7811`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1024
msgid ""
"If you are upgrading from version 3.1.2 or before, please also review the "
"release notes for 3.2.0 (included below)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1030
msgid "fish 3.2.0 (released March 1, 2021)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1035
msgid ""
"**Undo and redo support** for the command-line editor and pager search (:"
"issue:`1367`). By default, undo is bound to Control+Z, and redo to Alt+/."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1036
msgid ""
"**Builtins can now output before all data is read**. For example, ``string "
"replace`` no longer has to read all of stdin before it can begin to output. "
"This makes it usable also for pipes where the previous command hasn't "
"finished yet, like::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1039
msgid ""
"# Show all dmesg lines related to \"usb\"\n"
"dmesg -w | string match '*usb*'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1042
msgid ""
"**Prompts will now be truncated** instead of replaced with ``\"> \"`` if "
"they are wider than the terminal (:issue:`904`). For example::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1045
msgid "~/dev/build/fish-shell-git/src/fish-shell/build (makepkg)>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1047
msgid "will turn into::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1049
msgid "…h-shell/build (makepkg)>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1051
msgid ""
"It is still possible to react to the ``COLUMNS`` variable inside the prompt "
"to implement smarter behavior."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1052
msgid ""
"**fish completes ambiguous completions** after pressing :kbd:`Tab` even when "
"they have a common prefix, without the user having to press :kbd:`Tab` again "
"(:issue:`6924`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1055
msgid ""
"fish is less aggressive about resetting terminal modes, such as flow "
"control, after every command. Although flow control remains off by default, "
"enterprising users can now enable it with ``stty`` (:issue:`2315`, :issue:"
"`7704`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1058
msgid ""
"A new **\"fish_add_path\" helper function to add paths to $PATH** without "
"producing duplicates, to be used interactively or in ``config.fish`` (:issue:"
"`6960`, :issue:`7028`). For example::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1062
msgid "fish_add_path /opt/mycoolthing/bin"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1064
msgid ""
"will add /opt/mycoolthing/bin to the beginning of $fish_user_path without "
"creating duplicates, so it can be called safely from config.fish or "
"interactively, and the path will just be there, once."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1066
msgid "**Better errors with \"test\"** (:issue:`6030`)::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1068
msgid ""
"> test 1 = 2 and echo true or false\n"
"test: Expected a combining operator like '-a' at index 4\n"
"1 = 2 and echo true or echo false\n"
"      ^"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1073
msgid "This includes numbering the index from 1 instead of 0, like fish lists."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1074
msgid ""
"**A new theme for the documentation and Web-based configuration** (:issue:"
"`6500`, :issue:`7371`, :issue:`7523`), matching the design on fishshell.com."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1075
msgid ""
"``fish --no-execute`` **will no longer complain about unknown commands** or "
"non-matching wildcards, as these could be defined differently at runtime "
"(especially for functions). This makes it usable as a static syntax checker "
"(:issue:`977`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1078
msgid ""
"``string match --regex`` now integrates **named PCRE2 capture groups as fish "
"variables**, allowing variables to be set directly from ``string match`` (:"
"issue:`7459`). To support this functionality, ``string`` is now a reserved "
"word and can no longer be wrapped in a function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1079
msgid ""
"Globs and other **expansions are limited to 512,288 results** (:issue:"
"`7226`). Because operating systems limit the number of arguments to "
"commands, larger values are unlikely to work anyway, and this helps to avoid "
"hangs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1080
msgid ""
"A new **\"fish for bash users\" documentation page** gives a quick overview "
"of the scripting differences between bash and fish (:issue:`2382`), and the "
"completion tutorial has also been moved out into its own document (:issue:"
"`6709`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1083 ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1619
#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:2236
msgid "Syntax changes and new commands"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1085
msgid ""
"Range limits in index range expansions like ``$x[$start..$end]`` may be "
"omitted: ``$start`` and ``$end`` default to 1 and -1 (the last item) "
"respectively (:issue:`6574`)::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1087
msgid ""
"echo $var[1..]\n"
"echo $var[..-1]\n"
"echo $var[..]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1091
msgid "All print the full list ``$var``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1092
msgid ""
"When globbing, a segment which is exactly ``**`` may now match zero "
"directories. For example ``**/foo`` may match ``foo`` in the current "
"directory (:issue:`7222`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1097
msgid ""
"The ``type``, ``_`` (gettext), ``.`` (source) and ``:`` (no-op) functions "
"are now implemented builtins for performance purposes (:issue:`7342`, :issue:"
"`7036`, :issue:`6854`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1099
msgid ""
"``set`` and backgrounded jobs no longer overwrite ``$pipestatus`` (:issue:"
"`6820`), improving its use in command substitutions (:issue:`6998`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1100
msgid ""
"Computed (\"electric\") variables such as ``status`` are now only global in "
"scope, so ``set -Uq status`` returns false (:issue:`7032`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1101
msgid ""
"The output for ``set --show`` has been shortened, only mentioning the scopes "
"in which a variable exists (:issue:`6944`). In addition, it now shows if a "
"variable is a path variable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1103
msgid ""
"A new variable, ``fish_kill_signal``, is set to the signal that terminated "
"the last foreground job, or ``0`` if the job exited normally (:issue:"
"`6824`, :issue:`6822`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1104
msgid ""
"A new subcommand, ``string pad``, allows extending strings to a given width "
"(:issue:`7340`, :issue:`7102`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1105
msgid ""
"``string sub`` has a new ``--end`` option to specify the end index of a "
"substring (:issue:`6765`, :issue:`5974`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1107
msgid ""
"``string split`` has a new ``--fields`` option to specify fields to output, "
"similar to ``cut -f`` (:issue:`6770`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1109
msgid ""
"``string trim`` now also trims vertical tabs by default (:issue:`6795`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1110
msgid ""
"``string replace`` no longer prints an error if a capturing group wasn't "
"matched, instead treating it as empty (:issue:`7343`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1111
msgid ""
"``string`` subcommands now quit early when used with ``--quiet`` (:issue:"
"`7495`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1112
msgid ""
"``string repeat`` now handles multiple arguments, repeating each one (:issue:"
"`5988`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1113
msgid ""
"``printf`` no longer prints an error if not given an argument (not even a "
"format string)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1115
msgid ""
"The ``true`` and ``false`` builtins ignore any arguments, like other shells "
"(:issue:`7030`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1116
msgid ""
"``fish_indent`` now removes unnecessary quotes in simple cases (:issue:"
"`6722`) and gained a ``--check`` option to just check if a file is indented "
"correctly (:issue:`7251`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1118
msgid ""
"``fish_indent`` indents continuation lines that follow a line ending in a "
"backslash, ``|``, ``&&`` or ``||``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1119
msgid ""
"``pushd`` only adds a directory to the stack if changing to it was "
"successful (:issue:`6947`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1120
msgid ""
"A new ``fish_job_summary`` function is called whenever a background job "
"stops or ends, or any job terminates from a signal (:issue:`6959`, :issue:"
"`2727`, :issue:`4319`). The default behaviour can now be customized by "
"redefining it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1123
msgid ""
"``status`` gained new ``dirname`` and ``basename`` convenience subcommands "
"to get just the directory to the running script or the name of it, to "
"simplify common tasks such as running ``(dirname (status filename))`` (:"
"issue:`7076`, :issue:`1818`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1126
msgid ""
"Broken pipelines are now handled more smoothly; in particular, bad "
"redirection mid-pipeline results in the job continuing to run but with the "
"broken file descriptor replaced with a closed file descriptor. This allows "
"better error recovery and is more in line with other shells' behaviour (:"
"issue:`7038`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1130
msgid ""
"``jobs --quiet PID`` no longer prints \"no suitable job\" if the job for PID "
"does not exist (eg because it has finished) (:issue:`6809`, :issue:`6812`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1131
msgid "``jobs`` now shows continued child processes correctly (:issue:`6818`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1132
msgid ""
"``disown`` should no longer create zombie processes when job control is off, "
"such as in ``config.fish`` (:issue:`7183`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1133
msgid ""
"``command``, ``jobs`` and ``type`` builtins support ``--query`` as the long "
"form of ``-q``, matching other builtins. The long form ``--quiet`` is "
"deprecated (:issue:`7276`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1135
msgid ""
"``argparse`` no longer requires a short flag letter for long-only options (:"
"issue:`7585`) and only prints a backtrace with invalid options to argparse "
"itself (:issue:`6703`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1137
msgid ""
"``argparse`` now passes the validation variables (e.g. ``$_flag_value``) as "
"local-exported variables, avoiding the need for ``--no-scope-shadowing`` in "
"validation functions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1139
msgid ""
"``complete`` takes the first argument as the name of the command if the ``--"
"command``/``-c`` option is not used, so ``complete git`` is treated like "
"``complete --command git``, and it can show the loaded completions for "
"specific commands with ``complete COMMANDNAME`` (:issue:`7321`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1142
msgid ""
"``set_color -b`` (without an argument) no longer prints an error message, "
"matching other invalid invocations of this command (:issue:`7154`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1143
msgid ""
"``exec`` no longer produces a syntax error when the command cannot be found "
"(:issue:`6098`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1144
msgid ""
"``set --erase`` and ``abbr --erase`` can now erase multiple things in one "
"go, matching ``functions --erase`` (:issue:`7377`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1145
msgid ""
"``abbr --erase`` no longer prints errors when used with no arguments or on "
"an unset abbreviation (:issue:`7376`, :issue:`7732`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1146
msgid ""
"``test -t``, for testing whether file descriptors are connected to a "
"terminal, works for file descriptors 0, 1, and 2 (:issue:`4766`). It can "
"still return incorrect results in other cases (:issue:`1228`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1148
msgid ""
"Trying to execute scripts with Windows line endings (CRLF) produces a "
"sensible error (:issue:`2783`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1149
msgid ""
"Trying to execute commands with arguments that exceed the operating system "
"limit now produces a specific error (:issue:`6800`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1150
msgid ""
"An ``alias`` that delegates to a command with the same name no longer "
"triggers an error about recursive completion (:issue:`7389`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1151
msgid ""
"``math`` now has a ``--base`` option to output the result in hexadecimal or "
"octal (:issue:`7496`) and produces more specific error messages (:issue:"
"`7508`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1152
msgid ""
"``math`` learned bitwise functions ``bitand``, ``bitor`` and ``bitxor``, "
"used like ``math \"bitand(0xFE, 5)\"`` (:issue:`7281`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1153
msgid "``math`` learned tau for those who don't like typing \"2 * pi\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1154
msgid "Failed redirections will now set ``$status`` (:issue:`7540`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1155
msgid ""
"fish sets exit status in a more consistent manner after errors, including "
"invalid expansions like ``$foo[``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1156
msgid ""
"Using ``read --silent`` while fish is in private mode was adding these "
"potentially-sensitive entries to the history; this has been fixed (:issue:"
"`7230`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1157
msgid ""
"``read`` can now read interactively from other files, and can be used to "
"read from the terminal via ``read </dev/tty`` (if the operating system "
"provides ``/dev/tty``) (:issue:`7358`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1158
msgid ""
"A new ``fish_status_to_signal`` function for transforming exit statuses to "
"signal names has been added (:issue:`7597`, :issue:`7595`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1159
msgid ""
"The fallback ``realpath`` builtin supports the ``-s``/``--no-symlinks`` "
"option, like GNU realpath (:issue:`7574`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1160
msgid ""
"``functions`` and ``type`` now explain when a function was defined via "
"``source`` instead of just saying ``Defined in -``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1161
msgid ""
"Significant performance improvements when globbing, appending to variables "
"or in ``math``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1162
msgid ""
"``echo`` no longer interprets options at the beginning of an argument (eg "
"``echo \"-n foo\"``) (:issue:`7614`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1163
msgid ""
"fish now finds user configuration even if the ``HOME`` environment variable "
"is not set (:issue:`7620`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1164
msgid ""
"fish no longer crashes when started from a Windows-style working directory "
"(eg ``F:\\path``) (:issue:`7636`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1165
msgid ""
"``fish -c`` now reads the remaining arguments into ``$argv`` (:issue:`2314`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1166
msgid ""
"The ``pwd`` command supports the long options ``--logical`` and ``--"
"physical``, matching other implementations (:issue:`6787`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1167
msgid ""
"``fish --profile`` now only starts profiling after fish is ready to execute "
"commands (all configuration is completed). There is a new ``--profile-"
"startup`` option that only profiles the startup and configuration process (:"
"issue:`7648`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1168
msgid ""
"Builtins return a maximum exit status of 255, rather than potentially "
"overflowing. In particular, this affects ``exit``, ``return``, ``functions --"
"query``, and ``set --query`` (:issue:`7698`, :issue:`7702`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1169
msgid ""
"It is no longer an error to run builtin with closed stdin. For example "
"``count <&-`` now prints 0, instead of failing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1170
msgid ""
"Blocks, functions, and builtins no longer permit redirecting to file "
"descriptors other than 0 (standard input), 1 (standard output) and 2 "
"(standard error). For example, ``echo hello >&5`` is now an error. This "
"prevents corruption of internal state (:issue:`3303`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1175
msgid ""
"fish will now always attempt to become process group leader in interactive "
"mode (:issue:`7060`). This helps avoid hangs in certain circumstances, and "
"allows tmux's current directory introspection to work (:issue:`5699`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1176
msgid ""
"The interactive reader now allows ending a line in a logical operators "
"(``&&`` and ``||``) instead of complaining about a missing command. (This "
"was already syntactically valid, but interactive sessions didn't know about "
"it yet)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1177
msgid "The prompt is reprinted after a background job exits (:issue:`1018`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1178
msgid ""
"fish no longer inserts a space after a completion ending in ``.``, ``,`` or "
"``-`` is accepted, improving completions for tools that provide dynamic "
"completions (:issue:`6928`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1179
msgid ""
"If a filename is invalid when first pressing :kbd:`Tab`, but becomes valid, "
"it will be completed properly on the next attempt (:issue:`6863`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1180
msgid ""
"``help string match/replace/<subcommand>`` will show the help for string "
"subcommands (:issue:`6786`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1181
msgid ""
"``fish_key_reader`` sets the exit status to 0 when used with ``--help`` or "
"``--version`` (:issue:`6964`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1182
msgid ""
"``fish_key_reader`` and ``fish_indent`` send output from ``--version`` to "
"standard output, matching other fish binaries (:issue:`6964`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1183
msgid ""
"A new variable ``$status_generation`` is incremented only when the previous "
"command produces an exit status (:issue:`6815`). This can be used, for "
"example, to check whether a failure status is a holdover due to a background "
"job, or actually produced by the last run command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1184
msgid ""
"``fish_greeting`` is now a function that reads a variable of the same name, "
"and defaults to setting it globally. This removes a universal variable by "
"default and helps with updating the greeting. However, to disable the "
"greeting it is now necessary to explicitly specify universal scope (``set -U "
"fish_greeting``) or to disable it in config.fish (:issue:`7265`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1187
msgid "Events are properly emitted after a job is cancelled (:issue:`2356`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1188
msgid ""
"``fish_preexec`` and ``fish_postexec`` events are no longer triggered for "
"empty commands (:issue:`4829`, :issue:`7085`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1189
msgid ""
"Functions triggered by the ``fish_exit`` event are correctly run when the "
"terminal is closed or the shell receives SIGHUP (:issue:`7014`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1190 ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1418
msgid ""
"The ``fish_prompt`` event no longer fires when ``read`` is used. If you need "
"a function to run any time ``read`` is invoked by a script, use the new "
"``fish_read`` event instead (:issue:`7039`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1193
msgid ""
"A new ``fish_posterror`` event is emitted when attempting to execute a "
"command with syntax errors (:issue:`6880`, :issue:`6816`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1194
msgid ""
"The debugging system has now fully switched from the old numbered level to "
"the new named category system introduced in 3.1. A number of new debugging "
"categories have been added, including ``config``, ``path``, ``reader`` and "
"``screen`` (:issue:`6511`). See the output of ``fish --print-debug-"
"categories`` for the full list."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1195
msgid ""
"The warning about read-only filesystems has been moved to a new \"warning-"
"path\" debug category and can be disabled by setting a debug category of ``-"
"warning-path`` (:issue:`6630`)::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1198
msgid "fish --debug=-warning-path"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1200
msgid ""
"The enabled debug categories are now printed on shell startup (:issue:"
"`7007`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1201
msgid ""
"The ``-o`` short option to fish, for ``--debug-output``, works correctly "
"instead of producing an invalid option error (:issue:`7254`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1203
msgid ""
"fish's debugging can now also be enabled via ``FISH_DEBUG`` and "
"``FISH_DEBUG_OUTPUT`` environment variables. This helps with debugging when "
"no commandline options can be passed, like when fish is called in a shebang "
"(:issue:`7359`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1205
msgid ""
"Abbreviations are now expanded after all command terminators (eg ``;`` or ``|"
"``), not just space, as in fish 2.7.1 and before (:issue:`6970`), and after "
"closing a command substitution (:issue:`6658`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1207
msgid ""
"The history file is now created with user-private permissions, matching "
"other shells (:issue:`6926`). The directory containing the history file was "
"already private, so there should not have been any private data revealed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1211
msgid ""
"The output of ``time`` is now properly aligned in all cases (:issue:`6726`, :"
"issue:`6714`) and no longer depends on locale (:issue:`6757`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1212
msgid ""
"The command-not-found handling has been simplified. When it can't find a "
"command, fish now just executes a function called ``fish_command_not_found`` "
"instead of firing an event, making it easier to replace and reason about. "
"Previously-defined ``__fish_command_not_found_handler`` functions with an "
"appropriate event listener will still work (:issue:`7293`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1216
msgid ""
":kbd:`Control-C` handling has been reimplemented in C++ and is therefore "
"quicker (:issue:`5259`), no longer occasionally prints an \"unknown "
"command\" error (:issue:`7145`) or overwrites multiline prompts (:issue:"
"`3537`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1217
msgid ""
":kbd:`Control-C` no longer kills background jobs for which job control is "
"disabled, matching POSIX semantics (:issue:`6828`, :issue:`6861`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1219
msgid ""
"Autosuggestions work properly after :kbd:`Control-C` cancels the current "
"commmand line (:issue:`6937`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1220
msgid ""
"History search is now case-insensitive unless the search string contains an "
"uppercase character (:issue:`7273`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1221
msgid ""
"``fish_update_completions`` gained a new ``--keep`` option, which improves "
"speed by skipping completions that already exist (:issue:`6775`, :issue:"
"`6796`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1222
msgid ""
"Aliases containing an embedded backslash appear properly in the output of "
"``alias`` (:issue:`6910`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1223
msgid ""
"``open`` no longer hangs indefinitely on certain systems, as a bug in ``xdg-"
"open`` has been worked around (:issue:`7215`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1224
msgid ""
"Long command lines no longer add a blank line after execution (:issue:"
"`6826`) and behave better with :kbd:`Backspace` (:issue:`6951`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1225
msgid ""
"``functions -t`` works like the long option ``--handlers-type``, as "
"documented, instead of producing an error (:issue:`6985`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1226
msgid ""
"History search now flashes when it found no more results (:issue:`7362`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1227
msgid ""
"fish now creates the path in the environment variable ``XDG_RUNTIME_DIR`` if "
"it does not exist, before using it for runtime data storage (:issue:`7335`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1228
msgid ""
"``set_color --print-colors`` now also respects the bold, dim, underline, "
"reverse, italic and background modifiers, to better show their effect (:"
"issue:`7314`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1229
msgid ""
"The fish Web configuration tool (``fish_config``) shows prompts correctly on "
"Termux for Android (:issue:`7298`) and detects Windows Services for Linux 2 "
"properly (:issue:`7027`). It no longer shows the ``history`` variable as it "
"may be too large (one can use the History tab instead). It also starts the "
"browser in another thread, avoiding hangs in some circumstances, especially "
"with Firefox's Developer Edition (:issue:`7158`). Finally, a bug in the "
"Source Code Pro font may cause browsers to hang, so this font is no longer "
"chosen by default (:issue:`7714`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1230
msgid ""
"``funcsave`` gained a new ``--directory`` option to specify the location of "
"the saved function (:issue:`7041`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1231
msgid ""
"``help`` works properly on MSYS2 (:issue:`7113`) and only uses ``cmd.exe`` "
"if running on WSL (:issue:`6797`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1232
msgid ""
"Resuming a piped job by its number, like ``fg %1``, works correctly (:issue:"
"`7406`). Resumed jobs show the correct title in the terminal emulator (:"
"issue:`7444`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1233
msgid ""
"Commands run from key bindings now use the same TTY modes as normal commands "
"(:issue:`7483`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1234
msgid "Autosuggestions from history are now case-sensitive (:issue:`3978`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1235
msgid ""
"``$status`` from completion scripts is no longer passed outside the "
"completion, which keeps the status display in the prompt as the last "
"command's status (:issue:`7555`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1236
msgid "Updated localisations for pt_BR (:issue:`7480`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1237
msgid ""
"``fish_trace`` output now starts with ``->`` (like ``fish --profile``), "
"making the depth more visible (:issue:`7538`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1238
msgid ""
"Resizing the terminal window no longer produces a corrupted prompt (:issue:"
"`6532`, :issue:`7404`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1239
msgid ""
"``functions`` produces an error rather than crashing on certain invalid "
"arguments (:issue:`7515`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1240
msgid ""
"A crash in completions with inline variable assignment (eg ``A= b``) has "
"been fixed (:issue:`7344`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1241
msgid ""
"``fish_private_mode`` may now be changed dynamically using ``set`` (:issue:"
"`7589`), and history is kept in memory in private mode (but not stored "
"permanently) (:issue:`7590`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1242
msgid ""
"Commands with leading spaces may be retrieved from history with up-arrow "
"until a new command is run, matching zsh's ``HIST_IGNORE_SPACE`` (:issue:"
"`1383`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1243
msgid ""
"Importing bash history or reporting errors with recursive globs (``**``) no "
"longer hangs (:issue:`7407`, :issue:`7497`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1244
msgid ""
"``bind`` now shows ``\\x7f`` for the del key instead of a literal DEL "
"character (:issue:`7631`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1245
msgid ""
"Paths containing variables or tilde expansion are only suggested when they "
"are still valid (:issue:`7582`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1246
msgid ""
"Syntax highlighting can now color a command as invalid even if executed "
"quickly (:issue:`5912`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1247
msgid ""
"Redirection targets are no longer highlighted as error if they contain "
"variables which will likely be defined by the current commandline (:issue:"
"`6654`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1248
msgid ""
"fish is now more resilient against broken terminal modes (:issue:`7133`, :"
"issue:`4873`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1249
msgid ""
"fish handles being in control of the TTY without owning its own process "
"group better, avoiding some hangs in special configurations (:issue:`7388`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1250
msgid ""
"Keywords can now be colored differently by setting the "
"``fish_color_keyword`` variable (``fish_color_command`` is used as a "
"fallback) (:issue:`7678`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1251
msgid ""
"Just like ``fish_indent``, the interactive reader will indent continuation "
"lines that follow a line ending in a backslash, ``|``, ``&&`` or ``||`` (:"
"issue:`7694`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1252
msgid ""
"Commands with a trailing escaped space are saved in history correctly (:"
"issue:`7661`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1253
msgid ""
"``fish_prompt`` no longer mangles Unicode characters in the private-use "
"range U+F600-U+F700. (:issue:`7723`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1254
msgid ""
"The universal variable file, ``fish_variables``, can be made a symbolic link "
"without it being overwritten (:issue:`7466`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1255
msgid "fish is now more resilient against ``mktemp`` failing (:issue:`7482`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1261
msgid ""
"As mentioned above, new special input functions ``undo`` (:kbd:`Control+\\_` "
"or :kbd:`Control+Z`) and ``redo`` (:kbd:`Alt-/`) can be used to revert "
"changes to the command line or the pager search field (:issue:`6570`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1262
msgid ":kbd:`Control-Z` is now available for binding (:issue:`7152`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1263
msgid ""
"Additionally, using the ``cancel`` special input function (bound to :kbd:"
"`Escape` by default) right after fish picked an unambiguous completion will "
"undo that (:issue:`7433`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1264
msgid ""
"``fish_clipboard_paste`` (:kbd:`Control+V`) trims indentation from multiline "
"commands, because fish already indents (:issue:`7662`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1265
msgid ""
"Vi mode bindings now support ``dh``, ``dl``, ``c0``, ``cf``, ``ct``, ``cF``, "
"``cT``, ``ch``, ``cl``, ``y0``, ``ci``, ``ca``, ``yi``, ``ya``, ``di``, "
"``da``, ``d;``, ``d,``, ``o``, ``O`` and Control+left/right keys to navigate "
"by word (:issue:`6648`, :issue:`6755`, :issue:`6769`, :issue:`7442`, :issue:"
"`7516`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1266
msgid ""
"Vi mode bindings support :kbd:`~` (tilde) to toggle the case of the selected "
"character (:issue:`6908`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1267
msgid ""
"Functions ``up-or-search`` and ``down-or-search`` (:kbd:`Up` and :kbd:"
"`Down`) can cross empty lines, and don't activate search mode if the search "
"fails, which makes them easier to use to move between lines in some "
"situations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1268
msgid ""
"If history search fails to find a match, the cursor is no longer moved. This "
"is useful when accidentally starting a history search on a multi-line "
"commandline."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1269
msgid ""
"The special input function ``beginning-of-history`` (:kbd:`Page Up`) now "
"moves to the oldest search instead of the youngest - that's ``end-of-"
"history`` (:kbd:`Page Down`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1270
msgid ""
"A new special input function ``forward-single-char`` moves one character to "
"the right, and if an autosuggestion is available, only take a single "
"character from it (:issue:`7217`, :issue:`4984`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1271
msgid ""
"Special input functions can now be joined with ``or`` as a modifier (adding "
"to ``and``), though only some commands set an exit status (:issue:`7217`). "
"This includes ``suppress-autosuggestion`` to reflect whether an "
"autosuggestion was suppressed (:issue:`1419`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1272
msgid ""
"A new function ``__fish_preview_current_file``, bound to :kbd:`Alt+O`, opens "
"the current file at the cursor in a pager (:issue:`6838`, :issue:`6855`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1274
msgid ""
"``edit_command_buffer`` (:kbd:`Alt-E` and :kbd:`Alt-V`) passes the cursor "
"position to the external editor if the editor is recognized (:issue:`6138`, :"
"issue:`6954`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1276
msgid ""
"``__fish_prepend_sudo`` (:kbd:`Alt-S`) now toggles a ``sudo`` prefix (:issue:"
"`7012`) and avoids shifting the cursor (:issue:`6542`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1277
msgid ""
"``__fish_prepend_sudo`` (:kbd:`Alt-S`) now uses the previous commandline if "
"the current one is empty, to simplify rerunning the previous command with "
"``sudo`` (:issue:`7079`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1279
msgid ""
"``__fish_toggle_comment_commandline`` (:kbd:`Alt-#`) now uncomments and "
"presents the last comment from history if the commandline is empty (:issue:"
"`7137`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1281
msgid ""
"``__fish_whatis_current_token`` (:kbd:`Alt-W`) prints descriptions for "
"functions and builtins (:issue:`7191`, :issue:`2083`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1282
msgid ""
"The definition of \"word\" and \"bigword\" for movements was refined, fixing "
"(eg) vi mode's behavior with :kbd:`e` on the second-to-last char, and "
"bigword's behavior with single-character words and non-blank non-graphical "
"characters (:issue:`7353`, :issue:`7354`, :issue:`4025`, :issue:`7328`, :"
"issue:`7325`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1283
msgid ""
"fish's clipboard bindings now also support Windows Subsystem for Linux via "
"PowerShell and clip.exe (:issue:`7455`, :issue:`7458`) and will properly "
"copy newlines in multi-line commands."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1284
msgid ""
"Using the ``*-jump`` special input functions before typing anything else no "
"longer crashes fish."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1285
msgid ""
"Completing variable overrides (``foo=bar``) could replace the entire thing "
"with just the completion in some circumstances. This has been fixed (:issue:"
"`7398`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1290
msgid ""
"The default and example prompts print the correct exit status for commands "
"prefixed with ``not`` (:issue:`6566`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1292
msgid ""
"git prompts include all untracked files in the repository, not just those in "
"the current directory (:issue:`6086`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1294
msgid ""
"The git prompts correctly show stash states (:issue:`6876`, :issue:`7136`) "
"and clean states (:issue:`7471`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:1295
msgid ""
