#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3367
msgid "fish 2.1.2 (released Feb 24, 2015)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3369
msgid ""
"fish 2.1.2 contains a workaround for a filesystem bug in Mac OS X Yosemite. :"
"issue:`1859`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3372
msgid ""
"Specifically, after installing fish 2.1.1 and then rebooting, “Verify Disk” "
"in Disk Utility will report “Invalid number of hard links.” We don’t have "
"any reports of data loss or other adverse consequences. fish 2.1.2 avoids "
"triggering the bug, but does not repair an already affected filesystem. To "
"repair the filesystem, you can boot into Recovery Mode and use Repair Disk "
"from Disk Utility. Linux and versions of OS X prior to Yosemite are believed "
"to be unaffected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3380
msgid "There are no other changes in this release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3385
msgid "fish 2.1.1 (released September 26, 2014)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3387
msgid ""
"**Important:** if you are upgrading, stop all running instances of ``fishd`` "
"as soon as possible after installing this release; it will be restarted "
"automatically. On most systems, there will be no further action required. "
"Note that some environments (where ``XDG_RUNTIME_DIR`` is set), such as "
"Fedora 20, will require a restart of all running fish processes before "
"universal variables work as intended."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3394
msgid ""
"Distributors are highly encouraged to call ``killall fishd``, ``pkill "
"fishd`` or similar in installation scripts, or to warn their users to do so."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3399
msgid "Security fixes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3401
msgid ""
"The fish_config web interface now uses an authentication token to protect "
"requests and only responds to requests from the local machine with this "
"token, preventing a remote code execution attack. (closing CVE-2014-2914). :"
"issue:`1438`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3405
msgid ""
"``psub`` and ``funced`` are no longer vulnerable to attacks which allow "
"local privilege escalation and data tampering (closing CVE-2014-2906 and "
"CVE-2014-3856). :issue:`1437`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3408
msgid ""
"``fishd`` uses a secure path for its socket, preventing a local privilege "
"escalation attack (closing CVE-2014-2905). :issue:`1436`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3410
msgid ""
"``__fish_print_packages`` is no longer vulnerable to attacks which would "
"allow local privilege escalation and data tampering (closing "
"CVE-2014-3219). :issue:`1440`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3415
msgid "Other fixes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3417
msgid ""
"``fishd`` now ignores SIGPIPE, fixing crashes using tools like GNU Parallel "
"and which occurred more often as a result of the other ``fishd`` changes. :"
"issue:`1084` & :issue:`1690`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3424
msgid "fish 2.1.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3431
msgid "**Tab completions will fuzzy-match files.** :issue:`568`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3433
msgid ""
"When tab-completing a file, fish will first attempt prefix matches (``foo`` "
"matches ``foobar``), then substring matches (``ooba`` matches ``foobar``), "
"and lastly subsequence matches (``fbr`` matches ``foobar``). For example, in "
"a directory with files foo1.txt, foo2.txt, foo3.txt…, you can type only the "
"numeric part and hit tab to fill in the rest."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3440
msgid ""
"This feature is implemented for files and executables. It is not yet "
"implemented for options (like ``--foobar``), and not yet implemented across "
"path components (like ``/u/l/b`` to match ``/usr/local/bin``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3444
msgid ""
"**Redirections now work better across pipelines.** :issue:`110`, :issue:`877`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3446
msgid ""
"In particular, you can pipe stderr and stdout together, for example, with "
"``cmd ^&1 | tee log.txt``, or the more familiar ``cmd 2>&1 | tee log.txt``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3450
msgid ""
"**A single ``%`` now expands to the last job backgrounded.** :issue:`1008`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3452
msgid ""
"Previously, a single ``%`` would pid-expand to either all backgrounded jobs, "
"or all jobs owned by your user. Now it expands to the last job backgrounded. "
"If no job is in the background, it will fail to expand. In particular, ``fg "
"%`` can be used to put the most recent background job in the foreground."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3459 ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3576
msgid "Other Notable Fixes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3461
msgid ""
"alt-U and alt+C now uppercase and capitalize words, respectively. :issue:"
"`995`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3464
msgid "VTE based terminals should now know the working directory. :issue:`906`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3466
msgid "The autotools build now works on Mavericks. :issue:`968`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3468
msgid ""
"The end-of-line binding (ctrl+E) now accepts autosuggestions. :issue:`932`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3470
msgid ""
"Directories in ``/etc/paths`` (used on OS X) are now prepended instead of "
"appended, similar to other shells. :issue:`927`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3473
msgid ""
"Option-right-arrow (used for partial autosuggestion completion) now works on "
"iTerm2. :issue:`920`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3476
msgid ""
"Tab completions now work properly within nested subcommands. :issue:`913`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3478
msgid "``printf`` supports ``\\e``, the escape character. :issue:`910`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3480
msgid "``fish_config history`` no longer shows duplicate items. :issue:`900`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3482
msgid ""
"``$fish_user_paths`` is now prepended to $PATH instead of appended. :issue:"
"`888`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3485
msgid "Jobs complete when all processes complete. :issue:`876`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3487
msgid ""
"For example, in previous versions of fish, ``sleep 10 | echo Done`` returns "
"control immediately, because echo does not read from stdin. Now it does not "
"complete until sleep exits (presumably after 10 seconds)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3492
msgid "Better error reporting for square brackets. :issue:`875`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3494
msgid ""
"fish no longer tries to add ``/bin`` to ``$PATH`` unless PATH is totally "
"empty. :issue:`852`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3497
msgid ""
"History token substitution (alt-up) now works correctly inside subshells. :"
"issue:`833`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3500
msgid ""
"Flow control is now disabled, freeing up ctrl-S and ctrl-Q for other uses. :"
"issue:`814`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3503
msgid ""
"sh-style variable setting like ``foo=bar`` now produces better error "
"messages. :issue:`809`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3506
msgid "Commands with wildcards no longer produce autosuggestions. :issue:`785`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3508
msgid ""
"funced no longer freaks out when supplied with no arguments. :issue:`780`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3510
msgid ""
"fish.app now works correctly in a directory containing spaces. :issue:`774`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3512
msgid ""
"Tab completion cycling no longer occasionally fails to repaint. :issue:`765`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3514
msgid "Comments now work in eval’d strings. :issue:`684`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3516
msgid ""
"History search (up-arrow) now shows the item matching the autosuggestion, if "
"that autosuggestion was truncated. :issue:`650`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3519
msgid "Ctrl-T now transposes characters, as in other shells. :issue:`128`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3524
msgid "fish 2.0.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3531
msgid ""
"**Command substitutions now modify ``$status`` :issue:`547`.** Previously "
"the exit status of command substitutions (like ``(pwd)``) was ignored; "
"however now it modifies $status. Furthermore, the ``set`` command now only "
"sets $status on failure; it is untouched on success. This allows for the "
"following pattern:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3537
msgid ""
"if set python_path (which python)\n"
"   ...\n"
"end"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3543
msgid ""
"Because set does not modify $status on success, the if branch effectively "
"tests whether ``which`` succeeded, and if so, whether the ``set`` also "
"succeeded."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3547
msgid ""
"Improvements to PATH handling. There is a new variable, fish_user_paths, "
"which can be set universally, and whose contents are appended to $PATH :"
"issue:`527`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3551
msgid "/etc/paths and /etc/paths.d are now respected on OS X"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3552
msgid "fish no longer modifies $PATH to find its own binaries"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3554
msgid ""
"**Long lines no longer use ellipsis for line breaks**, and copy and paste "
"should no longer include a newline even if the line was broken :issue:`300`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3558
msgid ""
"**New syntax for index ranges** (sometimes known as “slices”) :issue:`212`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3560
msgid "**fish now supports an ``else if`` statement** :issue:`134`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3562
msgid "**Process and pid completion now works on OS X** :issue:`129`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3564
msgid ""
"**fish is now relocatable**, and no longer depends on compiled-in paths :"
"issue:`125`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3567
msgid ""
"**fish now supports a right prompt (RPROMPT)** through the fish_right_prompt "
"function :issue:`80`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3570
msgid ""
"**fish now uses posix_spawn instead of fork when possible**, which is much "
"faster on BSD and OS X :issue:`11`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3578
msgid "Updated VCS completions (darcs, cvs, svn, etc.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3579
msgid "Avoid calling getcwd on the main thread, as it can hang :issue:`696`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3580
msgid "Control-D (forward delete) no longer stops at a period :issue:`667`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3581
msgid "Completions for many new commands"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3582
msgid "fish now respects rxvt’s unique keybindings :issue:`657`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3583
msgid ""
"xsel is no longer built as part of fish. It will still be invoked if "
"installed separately :issue:`633`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3585
msgid "\\__fish_filter_mime no longer spews :issue:`628`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3586
msgid ""
"The –no-execute option to fish no longer falls over when reaching the end of "
"a block :issue:`624`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3588
msgid ""
"fish_config knows how to find fish even if it’s not in the $PATH :issue:`621`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3589
msgid ""
"A leading space now prevents writing to history, as is done in bash and zsh :"
"issue:`615`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3591
msgid ""
"Hitting enter after a backslash only goes to a new line if it is followed by "
"whitespace or the end of the line :issue:`613`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3593
msgid "printf is now a builtin :issue:`611`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3594
msgid ""
"Event handlers should no longer fire if signals are blocked :issue:`608`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3595
msgid "set_color is now a builtin :issue:`578`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3596
msgid ""
"man page completions are now located in a new generated_completions "
"directory, instead of your completions directory :issue:`576`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3598
msgid "tab now clears autosuggestions :issue:`561`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3599
msgid ""
"tab completion from within a pair of quotes now attempts to “appropriate” "
"the closing quote :issue:`552`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3601
msgid ""
"$EDITOR can now be a list: for example, ``set EDITOR gvim -f``) :issue:`541`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3602
msgid "``case`` bodies are now indented :issue:`530`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3603
msgid "The profile switch ``-p`` no longer crashes :issue:`517`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3604
msgid "You can now control-C out of ``read`` :issue:`516`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3605
msgid "``umask`` is now functional on OS X :issue:`515`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3606
msgid "Avoid calling getpwnam on the main thread, as it can hang :issue:`512`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3607
msgid ""
"Alt-F or Alt-right-arrow (Option-F or option-right-arrow) now accepts one "
"word of an autosuggestion :issue:`435`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3609
msgid "Setting fish as your login shell no longer kills OpenSUSE :issue:`367`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3610
msgid ""
"Backslashes now join lines, instead of creating multiple commands :issue:"
"`347`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3612
msgid "echo now implements the -e flag to interpret escapes :issue:`337`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3613
msgid ""
"When the last token in the user’s input contains capital letters, use its "
"case in preference to that of the autosuggestion :issue:`335`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3615
msgid "Descriptions now have their own muted color :issue:`279`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3616
msgid ""
"Wildcards beginning with a . (for example, ``ls .*``) no longer match . "
"and .. :issue:`270`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3618
msgid "Recursive wildcards now handle symlink loops :issue:`268`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3619
msgid ""
"You can now delete history items from the fish_config web interface :issue:"
"`250`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3621
msgid ""
"The OS X build now weak links ``wcsdup`` and ``wcscasecmp`` :issue:`240`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3622
msgid ""
"fish now saves and restores the process group, which prevents certain "
"processes from being erroneously reported as stopped :issue:`197`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3624
msgid "funced now takes an editor option :issue:`187`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3625
msgid ""
"Alternating row colors are available in fish pager through "
"``fish_pager_color_secondary`` :issue:`186`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3627
msgid ""
"Universal variable values are now stored based on your MAC address, not your "
"hostname :issue:`183`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3629
msgid ""
"The caret ^ now only does a stderr redirection if it is the first character "
"of a token, making git users happy :issue:`168`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3631
msgid "Autosuggestions will no longer cause line wrapping :issue:`167`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3632
msgid "Better handling of Unicode combining characters :issue:`155`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3633
msgid "fish SIGHUPs processes more often :issue:`138`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3634
msgid "fish no longer causes ``sudo`` to ask for a password every time"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3635
msgid "fish behaves better under Midnight Commander :issue:`121`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3636
msgid "``set -e`` no longer crashes :issue:`100`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3637
msgid ""
"fish now will automatically import history from bash, if there is no fish "
"history :issue:`66`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3639
msgid ""
"Backslashed-newlines inside quoted strings now behave more intuitively :"
"issue:`52`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3641
msgid "Tab titles should be shown correctly in iTerm2 :issue:`47`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3642
msgid "scp remote path completion now sometimes works :issue:`42`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3643
msgid "The ``read`` builtin no longer shows autosuggestions :issue:`29`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3644
msgid ""
"Custom key bindings can now be set via the ``fish_user_key_bindings`` "
"function :issue:`21`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3646
msgid ""
"All Python scripts now run correctly under both Python 2 and Python 3 :issue:"
"`14`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3648
msgid "The “accept autosuggestion” key can now be configured :issue:`19`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3649
msgid "Autosuggestions will no longer suggest invalid commands :issue:`6`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3654
msgid "fishfish Beta r2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3657
msgid "Bug Fixes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3659
msgid ""
"**Implicit cd** is back, for paths that start with one or two dots, a slash, "
"or a tilde."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3661
msgid ""
"**Overrides of default functions should be fixed.** The “internalized "
"scripts” feature is disabled for now."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3663
msgid ""
"**Disabled delayed suspend.** This is a strange job-control feature of BSD "
"systems, including OS X. Disabling it frees up Control Y for other purposes; "
"in particular, for yank, which now works on OS X."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3666
msgid ""
"**fish_indent is fixed.** In particular, the ``funced`` and ``funcsave`` "
"functions work again."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3668
msgid ""
"A SIGTERM now ends the whole execution stack again (resolving :issue:`13`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3669
msgid ""
"Bumped the \\__fish_config_interactive version number so the default "
"fish_color_autosuggestion kicks in."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3671
msgid ""
"fish_config better handles combined term256 and classic colors like “555 "
"yellow”."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3675 ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3700
msgid "New Features"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3677
msgid ""
"**A history builtin**, and associated interactive function that enables "
"deleting history items. Example usage: \\* Print all history items beginning "
"with echo: ``history --prefix echo`` \\* Print all history items containing "
"foo: ``history --contains foo`` \\* Interactively delete some items "
"containing foo: ``history --delete --contains foo``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3684
msgid "Credit to @siteshwar for implementation. Thanks @siteshwar!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3689
msgid "fishfish Beta r1"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3692
msgid "Scripting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3694
msgid ""
"No changes! All existing fish scripts, config files, completions, etc. from "
"trunk should continue to work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3702
msgid ""
"**Autosuggestions**. Think URL fields in browsers. When you type a command, "
"fish will suggest the rest of the command after the cursor, in a muted gray "
"when possible. You can accept the suggestion with the right arrow key or "
"Ctrl-F. Suggestions come from command history, completions, and some custom "
"code for cd; there’s a lot of potential for improvement here. The "
"suggestions are computed on a background pthread, so they never slow down "
"your typing. The autosuggestion feature is incredible. I miss it dearly "
"every time I use anything else."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3712
msgid ""
"**term256 support** where available, specifically modern xterms and OS X "
"Lion. You can specify colors the old way (‘set_color cyan’) or by specifying "
"RGB hex values (‘set_color FF3333’); fish will pick the closest supported "
"color. Some xterms do not advertise term256 support either in the $TERM or "
"terminfo max_colors field, but nevertheless support it. For that reason, "
"fish will default into using it on any xterm (but it can be disabled with an "
"environment variable)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3720
msgid ""
"**Web-based configuration** page. There is a new function ‘fish_config’. "
"This spins up a simple Python web server and opens a browser window to it. "
"From this web page, you can set your shell colors and view your functions, "
"variables, and history; all changes apply immediately to all running shells. "
"Eventually all configuration ought to be supported via this mechanism (but "
"in addition to, not instead of, command line mechanisms)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3728
msgid ""
"**Man page completions**. There is a new function ‘fish_update_completions’. "
"This function reads all the man1 files from your manpath, removes the roff "
"formatting, parses them to find the commands and options, and outputs fish "
"completions into ~/.config/fish/completions. It won’t overwrite existing "
"completion files (except ones that it generated itself)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3736
msgid "Programmatic Changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3738
msgid ""
"fish is now entirely in C++. I have no particular love for C++, but it "
"provides a ready memory-model to replace halloc. We’ve made an effort to "
"keep it to a sane and portable subset (no C++11, no boost, no going crazy "
"with templates or smart pointers), but we do use the STL and a little tr1."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3743
msgid ""
"halloc is entirely gone, replaced by normal C++ ownership semantics. If you "
"don’t know what halloc is, well, now you have two reasons to be happy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3746
msgid ""
"All the crufty C data structures are entirely gone. array_list_t, "
"priority_queue_t, hash_table_t, string_buffer_t have been removed and "
"replaced by STL equivalents like std::vector, std::map, and std::wstring. A "
"lot of the string handling now uses std::wstring instead of wchar_t \\*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3751
msgid ""
"fish now spawns pthreads for tasks like syntax highlighting that require "
"blocking I/O."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3753
msgid ""
"History has been completely rewritten. History files now use an extensible "
"YAML-style syntax. History “merging” (multiple shells writing to the same "
"history file) now works better. There is now a maximum history length of "
"about 250k items (256 \\* 1024)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3757
msgid "The parser has been “instanced,” so you can now create more than one."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3758
msgid "Total #LoC has shrunk slightly even with the new features."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3761
msgid "Performance"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3763
msgid ""
"fish now runs syntax highlighting in a background thread, so typing commands "
"is always responsive even on slow filesystems."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3765
msgid "echo, test, and pwd are now builtins, which eliminates many forks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGELOG.rst:3766
msgid ""
"The files in share/functions and share/completions now get ‘internalized’ "
"into C strings that get compiled in with fish. This substantially reduces "
"the number of files touched at startup. A consequence is that you cannot "
"change these functions without recompiling, but often other functions depend "
"on these “standard” functions, so changing them is perhaps not a good idea "
"anyways."
msgstr ""

